South America
---
[2] Colombia (Boyacá department)
Date: Mon 2 Apr 2018 6:51 AM COT
Source: LA FM [in Spanish, trans., edited]
https://www.lafm.com.co/salud/analizan-tres-casos-de-sarampion-en-boyaca/


Boyacá is the model department at the national level in epidemiological surveillance, which is why monitoring is carried out in relation to vaccination processes.

Germán Pertúz, secretary of health of Boyacá, confirmed to the LA FM that 3 minors of the municipalities of Tunja, Duitama, and Sogamoso, presented with the symptoms of measles. For this reason samples were taken and sent to the National Institute of Health for biological testing

The Secretary of Health recalled that an inspection process has been started in each of the municipalities of the department, because of the massive influx of Venezuelans.

"Thanks to that we were able to identify these 3 minors, 1 in Tunja seen in the Colsubsidio clinic, another minor in the Boyacá clinic in Duitama, and another minor in the Valle del Sol clinic in Sogamoso."

Following the sanitary health protocols for this type of procedure, the samples were transferred under strict security measures, to avoid that any agent alter the results on the study of these cases of measles.

"The samples were immediately taken and transported to the National Institute of Health," said Pertúz to LA FM. If the result is positive, the official said that efforts will be redoubled with the national vaccination day that will take place during the month [April 2018].

