[3] Colombia (Quindío department)
Date: Mon 2 Apr 2018 07:07 COT
Source: Caracol Radio [in Spanish, trans., edited]
http://caracol.com.co/emisora/2018/04/02/armenia/1522669483_775617.html


The secretary of health of Quindío department Cesar Augusto Rincón confirmed that the results of only 3 cases are still pending from the National Institute of Health, to determine if measles is present in the region or not. However, work is being done to enforce the vaccination scheme for minors who do not have it. "We already have the report of the National Institute of Health that 4 of the samples are negative for rubella and measles, but this does not mean that we are going to lower our guard; on the contrary, we have all the available equipment", said the secretary of health.

The official however stressed that the vaccination coverage in Quindío is 95 percent, without ignoring that there are children less than 5 years who are not fully vaccinated.

